org.eclipse.viatra.dse.solutionstore

Class DummySolutionStore

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.eclipse.viatra.dse.solutionstore.DummySolutionStore
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISolutionStore

    public class DummySolutionStore
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISolutionStore
    An empty implementation of ISolutionStore which doesn't store any solution. Useful when the framework is extended in such a way, that the solutions are stored elsewhere and in other structure.
    Author:
    Andras Szabolcs Nagy

      • newSolution

        public ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType newSolution(ThreadContext context)
        Description copied from interface: ISolutionStore
        Notifies the solution store of a potential solution trajectory. Note that the objectives will never be null and the implementation should be thread safe.

        Also it determines whether the execution should stop or not, if a solution is found. It can have three different responses:

        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.CONTINUE: the execution should continue.
        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.STOP_THREAD: this execution thread should be stopped while the others can continue.
        • ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType.STOP_ALL: the whole design space exploration process should exit.
        Specified by:
        newSolution in interface ISolutionStore
        Parameters:
        context - Context with the actual state of the exploration process.
        Returns:
        The ISolutionStore.StopExecutionType based on it's internal reasoning.
